				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmmm,<BR>
I'm gunna apologize for my previous post, I hate it when folks post inane-nontopical stuff, and I just full on did that.<BR>
<BR>
Back to Ignite blood, The reason it's a great spell and why we don't care that it takes 2 mins to kick in, is because Ignite blood doesn't give a root-break chance. Yes, Ice comet will do lotsa damage lotsa times, meanwhile you break root on a solo mob and he greases his treads on your frail body. Meanwhile, mr. Necro is firing of Dot #5 (Kinna like Aftershave), while the Mob slowly dies from the inside out, whilst we sit down and meditate :).  <BR>
<BR>
And if you're outdoors, it gets REALLY painful for the mobs: Cascading Darkness, Invoke Fear, Lich, Scourge, Asystole, Ignite Blood, Bond of Death, VOS, maybe a pet if yer feeling real mean. :). Anyway, there's about 5000 damage in 2 mins (Some of the spells can be recast due to short duration times (VoS, Asystole, Darkness). And yes, a wizard with massive mana can maybe get 4 Ice comets off in 45 seconds, but they, they're oom and probably dead from Overburn (Mob Frenzy), meanwhile, we're at almost Full mana, and the mob has probably barely laid a hand on us.<BR>
<BR>
Darnalak Carcophan<BR>
DeathMaster -- Veeshan.<BR>
<BR>
Disclaimer: Of course, it's never this easy :) as many necros will attest after having Invoke fear #3 resisted, and bein jackslapped for 600 pts every 2 rounds :) don'tcha just love shamans with SOW? (hint)
