				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Fizbanilus, I know that tactic from experience. I (a lvl 42 necro) dueled my lvl 40 wizard friend and he killed me in one whole minute - if that! He started by immediately casting his root spell, with a one second casting time, on my pet,i.e., Pet out of action unless you have a cancel magic ready to cast on it. Meanwhile, I cast fear and he resisted due to his high magic resistance. Of course, the IC came next - BAM! I cast fear again - fizzle; IC - BAM! At this point he has taken at least half my health, with pet still sitting there looking stupid at my wizard friend who stepped back just out of the pet's range. I lifetap to get a little health back, but his IC is cast too fast and yes, BAM! One more fear which is resisted and IC - BAM! DEAD NECRO! The pet never even got one hit in!!!<BR>
Now I will be the first to say that I am terrible at dueling and that the outcome very well could have been different with an experienced necro (or &quot;smart&quot; for that matter, although i resent the idea that I am a stupid player just because I don't know how to duel - I have done it twice =)) If dueling were the end all for me, I would probably join all the teenie boppers on Unreal Tournament or Quake III. Personally, I like a group with Shaman/Clerics, Tanks, Necro/enchanter, and Wizzie (Nuker) =).  Its amazing what you can do with a well-balanced grop.<BR>
<BR>
P.S. Any ideas on how to change my strategy against the Wizzie, feel free to post it on up! I would love to get even with him! Muahahaha!
